        <h1 id="offer-title">Shedding Light on Light Pollution</h1>
        <div class="offer-item">
          <h3>What is Light Pollution?</h3>
          <p>Light pollution is the excessive or misdirected artificial light produced by human activity. It not only obscures the stars and celestial bodies in the night sky but also disrupts ecosystems, affects human health, and wastes energy.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="offer-item">
          <h3>Causes of Light Pollution</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Urbanization</li>
                <li>Outdoor Lighting Practices</li>
                <li>Advertising and Signage</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="offer-item">
          <h3>Effects of Light Pollution</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Disrupted Ecosystems</li>
                <li>Health Impacts</li>
                <li>Disruption of Astronomical Observations</li>
                <li>Energy Waste</li>
                <li>Loss of Cultural Heritage</li>
                
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="offer-item">
          <h3>Solutions to Light Pollution</h3>
            <p>Light pollution is a widespread and growing problem with significant environmental, health, and cultural implications. However, we can minimize its impacts and preserve the beauty of the night sky for future generations by implementing the following solutions:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Use Dark-Sky-Friendly Lighting</li>
                <li>Light Regulations</li>
                <li>Public Awareness and Education</li>
                <li>Adaptive Lighting Technology</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

